cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use AlphaFold Sovereign MCP in research, please cite it
  using the metadata below. For citations of specific data sources
  accessed through this software (AlphaFold DB, UniProt, etc.)
  please also cite those sources according to their own citation
  requirements.
type: software
title: "AlphaFold Sovereign MCP"
abstract: >-
  An open-source Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that exposes
  AlphaFold DB and 8 other public biomedical data sources (Open
  Targets, ChEMBL, Ensembl VEP, ClinVar, gnomAD, MONDO, HPO,
  DisGeNET)
  as tool calls a Claude (or other MCP-capable) client can invoke
  directly. Tool results can be persisted to a local SQLite knowledge graph
  via its storage API; the exposed MCP tools query and export that store
  read-only (automatic per-invocation persistence is not yet wired). The
  server is engineering-validated (697 tests, 100%
  line + branch coverage) but its scientific outputs — draft ACMG/AMP
  evidence and a heuristic druggability tier — have NOT been reviewed
  by independent domain experts and must be treated as research aids,
  not as clinical decision support. See LIMITATIONS.md.
